        "subject": "LU-19820 build: fix ofa_kernel detection error",
        "message": "LU-19820 build: fix ofa_kernel detection error\n\nStarting with recent DOCA packaging, for some of them,\nthe kernel include directory for ofa_kernel is now a symlink,\nwhich is causing a `find` command to fail.\n\nAdd -H to ensure find follow that path if this is a symlink.\n\nChange-Id: Id72634045b3e6af577413b9ae3812d07420fe07e\nSigned-off-by: Aurelien Degremont <adegremont@nvidia.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63536\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nReviewed-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
